ERROR:ASSIGN_IN_IF: do not use assignment in if condition
#54: FILE: drivers/infiniband/hw/mthca/mthca_eq.c:369:
+	if ((ecr = readl(dev->ecr_base + 4)) != 0) {

Do not use assignments in if condition.
Example::

  if ((foo = bar(...)) < BAZ) {

should be written as::

  foo = bar(...);
  if (foo < BAZ) {

CHECK:LINE_SPACING: Please don't use multiple blank lines
#95: FILE: drivers/infiniband/hw/mthca/mthca_main.c:724:
 
+

Vertical space is wasted given the limited number of lines an
editor window can display when multiple blank lines are used.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

WARNING:HOTPLUG_SECTION: Using __devinit is unnecessary
#167: FILE: drivers/infiniband/hw/mthca/mthca_main.c:781:
 static int __devinit mthca_enable_msi_x(struct mthca_dev *mdev)

WARNING:SPLIT_STRING: quoted string split across lines
#195: FILE: drivers/infiniband/hw/mthca/mthca_main.c:961:
+		mthca_err(mdev, "Couldn't map ecr register, "
+			  "aborting.\n");

Quoted strings that appear as messages in userspace and can be
grepped, should not be split across multiple lines.

See: https://lore.kernel.org/lkml/20120203052727.GA15035@leaf/

